<p><strong>Dragonscale Blade</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Katanas" href="/Katanas" target="">Katana</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Dragonscale Blade</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>, with reduced scaling in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength">Strength</a>, and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for dealing&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Slash Damage" href="/Slash+Damage" target="">Slash</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Pierce Damage" href="/Pierce+Damage" target="">Pierce</a>&nbsp;damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lightning Damage" href="/Lightning+Damage">Lightning</a>-susceptible enemies.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>A weapon made by sharpening a Gravel Stone scale, thought to be<br>the source of ancient dragon immortality, into an unclouded<br>blade.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Alas, the Dragonkin Soldiers never attained immortality, and<br>perished as decrepit, pale imitations of their skyborn kin.</em>&nbsp;</p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Dragonscale Blade in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Dragonscale Blade weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Drops from&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dragonkin Soldier" href="/Dragonkin+Soldier">Dragonkin Soldier</a>&nbsp;in the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring lake of rot" href="/lake+of+rot">Lake of Rot</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=6404&amp;lat=-134.7875&amp;lng=63.412853&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB" href="/Interactive+Map?id=6404&amp;lat=-134.7875&amp;lng=63.412853&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB">Elden Ring Map Link</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Dragonscale Blade Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ice Lightning Sword" href="/Ice+Lightning+Sword" target="">Ice Lightning Sword</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>Can't be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a> nor boosted by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Dragonscale Blade</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Guard Boost goes from 32 to 30 at +10</li> 
 <li>Deals +20% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#dragon"><img title="Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Dragon</a>&nbsp;type enemies</li> 
 <li>Deals +10% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#ancient-dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#ancient-dragon"><img title="Ancient Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/ancient-dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="ancient dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Ancient Dragon</a>&nbsp;type enemies</li> 
 <li>Do note however, that Dragons typically have high resistance for&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring damage types" href="/damage+types">slash-type</a> damage. The Dragonscale Blade moveset consists almost entirely of slash attacks (except running attack and 1h heavy). As a result, this weapon is not optimal for slaying dragons and magma wyrms and may be outperformed by a regular spear or thrusting sword of the same upgrade level.</li> 
 <li>When the weapon skill is activated, the sword gets temporarily buffed with additional <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lightning Damage" href="/Lightning+Damage">Lightning</a>&nbsp;damage, and a passive <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Frostbite" href="/Frostbite" target="">Frostbite</a> buildup. <em>The blue lightning does regular lightning damage</em>.</li> 
 <li>Ice Lightning effect from the AoW lasts&nbsp;45 seconds.</li> 
 <li>Buff adds 160 flat Lightning Damage to weapon ar and 80 frost build up.</li> 
 <li>The pommel resembles the head of a Dragonkin.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes">Runes</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
