				<li id="16694559" class="cmnt-root" data="2" data-d="1653359912000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t576362/Dragonscale-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">23 May 2022 22:38</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16694559" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">My build is a katana user, dex-faith.  Have the uchigatana, yura&apos;s katana, and a few others.  The weapon art on this one is very very precise, you can easily miss of not spot-on.  But when it hits it&apos;s good for shield enemies, like those golden dragon knights.  Usually the are super tanky, but if you catch them even once when they start to attack they go down to half health (the frostbite procs on roughly the second hit).  I tested it non-upgraded in limgrave on the heavy-shield knight in front of the gate, then on the golden dragon knight in lurnia east, and again on one in altus plateau.  The altus one even melted from it.  It takes some practice for the timing and reach, but it has a place in my line up.  Unsheathe and piercing fang have their place as well, but the lightning ice is now a fantastic addition at +8.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16694559" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16694559" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphi